    "Kuźba and Biecek (2020) also focus on explaining black box ML classifications.",
    "They leverage BreakDown Charts (Gosiewska and Biecek 2019) to answer \"Why\" questions Studies that did employ model-agnostic explanations were omitted 1 3 and highlight influential features.",
    "Moreover, they use Ceteris Paribus analysis (Kuźba et al. 2019) to answer What-if questions and provide a broader context of the model's behavior.",
    "In the domain of decision support systems, Valmeekam et al. (2021) employ contrastive or minimally complete explanations (Chakraborti et al. 2017) to explain the suggested plans.",
    "They specifically target \"Why\" and \"Why not\" questions and allow the user to propose alternative plans to solicit feedback."
